linkedlist package¶

linkedlist.linkedlist module¶

class linkedlist.linkedlist.linkedlist[source]¶

Bases: object

The linkedlist class holds a collection of characters using a linked list of nodes. It includes methods that allow the linkedlist to be manipulated and modified.

__init__()[source]¶

Constructs an empty linkedlist.

size()[source]¶

Returns the number of nodes in this linkedlist.

Returns:

int: number of nodes

getHead()[source]¶

Returns a reference to the head of the calling linkedlist.

Returns:

linkedlist: reference to the head of the calling linkedlist

getTail()[source]¶

Returns a reference to the tail of the calling linkedlist.

Returns:

linkedlist: reference to the tail of the calling linkedlist

add(element)[source]¶

Adds a node that contains the specified character to the head of the calling linkedlist if the head is None, else it adds the node to the tail.

Args:

element (str): specified character

addMany(*args)[source]¶

Adds a variable number of nodes that contain the specified characters to the head of the calling linkedlist if the head is equal to None, else it adds them to the tail.

addAll(addend)[source]¶

Adds the contents of the specified linkedlist to the end of the calling linkedlist.

Args:

addend (linkedlist): specified linkedlist

Raises:

ValueError: indicates addend is None

remove(target)[source]¶

Removes a node containing the specified target from the calling linkedlist.

Args:

target (str): specified target

Returns:

Boolean: False if the specified target exists in the calling linkedlist, else True

Returns the data values in the calling linkedlist.

Returns:

str: data values in the calling linkedlist

Tests if the calling linkedlist is equal to the specified object.

Boolean: True if the calling linkedlist is equal to the specified object, else False
